Package ohos.rpc

Class IPCSkeleton

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.rpc.IPCSkeleton

  • public class IPCSkeleton
extends Object
    Provides static interfaces in the IPC skeleton to obtain services, read and write objects, obtain the UID and PID, obtain the IDs of local and peer devices, and check whether an interface call is made on the same device.
    Since:
    1

      • getCallingPid

        public static int getCallingPid​()
        Obtains the PID of a proxy.

        This method is static. The PID is a positive integer during the communication between the RemoteProxy object and RemoteObject object, and resumes to 0 when the communication ends. If this method is called from the RemoteProxy object, 0 is returned; if this method is called from the RemoteObject object, the PID of the corresponding RemoteProxy object is returned.

        Returns:
        Returns the PID of the proxy.
        Since:
        1

      • getCallingUid

        public static int getCallingUid​()
        Obtains the UID of a proxy.

        This method is static. The UID is a positive integer during the communication between the RemoteProxy object and RemoteObject object, and resumes to 0 when the communication ends. If this method is called from the RemoteProxy object, 0 is returned; if this method is called from the RemoteObject object, the UID of the corresponding RemoteProxy object is returned.

        Returns:
        Returns the UID of the proxy.

      • flushCommands

        public static int flushCommands​(IRemoteObject object)
        Flushes all pending commands from a specified RemoteProxy to the corresponding RemoteObject.

        This method is static. You are advised to call this method before performing any time-sensitive operations.

        Parameters:
        object - Indicates the specified RemoteProxy.
        Returns:
        Returns 0 if the operation succeeds; returns an error code if the input object is empty or RemoteObject, or the operation fails.
        Since:
        1

      • resetCallingIdentity

        public static String resetCallingIdentity​()
        Replaces the UID and PID of the remote user with those of the local user.

        This method is static. It can be used in scenarios like authentication.

        Returns:
        Returns a string containing the UID and PID of the remote user.
        Since:
        1

      • setCallingIdentity

        public static boolean setCallingIdentity​(String identity)
        Restores the UID and PID to those of the remote user.

        This method is static. It is usually called after resetCallingIdentity is used and requires the UID and PID of the remote user returned by resetCallingIdentity.

        Parameters:
        identity - Indicates the string containing the UID and PID of the remote user, which is returned by resetCallingIdentity.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the operation succeeds; returns false otherwise.
        Since:
        1
